review_blob: I really liked this one.... Brown-reddish color. Tan medium head. Citrus aroma, grapefruit. Taste is hoppy, citrus, and not too much alcohol. You cannot tell its 9%. A bit sweet. Nice after taste of bitter and grapefruit... Even though this is not IPA there is a bit of the IPA-citrus-hoppy taste I love.. This is one I would buy again.

OMG.... what an awesome beer. Smells of chocolate, Vanilla, coffee and dark fruit... Taste is awesome, texture is creamy. Chocolate, Coffee, Vanilla and hints of liqorice. Sweet....You do feel the alcohol a bit but it wears off after a few sips... Little bitter aftertaste. Really, really good!!! Will absolutely buy again....

Very dark, tan or even brown head. Smells of chocolate and coffee, also hints of dark fruit. Taste was o.k. at first but then got better by each sip. Pretty good beer. It is sweet, chocolaty but not over the top, but also a bit hoppy and bitter aftertaste which I liked. Also heavy roasted coffee. Oily texture.
